South Africa’s AB de Villiers File picture: Getty Images
AB de Villiers scored 10 fewer runs than Quinton de Kock’s career-best 59 for South Africa in the first T20 against Bangladesh in Bloemfontein on Thursday‚ but De Villiers probably had the greater influence on his team’s performance.
He faced 27 balls for his 49‚ which brimmed with innovative strokeplay and audacious footwork along with eight fours. And he had fun.
“I enjoy what I do‚” De Villiers said. “I love playing cricket‚ and I love contributing to the team and scoring runs and having impactful innings.”
Thursday’s game was De Villiers’s fourth for South Africa since he withdrew from the test series in England in July and August.


But in those four matches, he has improved his career-best one-day score to 176 and delivered Thursday’s cracking cameo.
The break from the team environment seems to have done him good. “I love working by myself and I had the opportunity to do that‚” he said.
De Villiers’s latest innings helped South Africa total 195/4 and curb Bangladesh’s reply to 175/9.
That sets up the home side for a clean sweep of the Bangladeshis in the second T20 in Potchefstroom tomorrow. – TimesLIVE


